<subSubSection id="DFF2D27C970415350B64072253D250B7" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="ED636D088616712EC4BF27F6726B7A7A" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="056427B9C4EC9D4C7F9E4EFF402A4E15" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">
<taxonomicName id="D5D9B5E227AFC621F3E87070CBB2D1CE" authorityName="Droissart, Stevart &amp; P. J. Cribb" authorityYear="2014" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Distylodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sonkeanum">
<emphasis id="266A22CCE1D58003D26C86432706A8CF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Distylodon sonkeanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Droissart, 
<normalizedToken id="393B6F4DE03146A5771FB5C5517D641A" originalValue="Stévart">Stevart</normalizedToken>
&amp; P.J.Cribb, is close to 
<taxonomicName id="2F208CE76FECA51A11B85DE95B95C05F" authorityName="Summerh" authorityYear="1966" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Distylodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="27" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="comptum">
<emphasis id="C85700FE9232182F59B0606C17CCC09C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="27">Distylodon comptum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Summerh. but differs from it in having several-flowered inflorescences, longer leaves and spur, and shorter pedicel and ovary.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
