<subSubSection id="18AEDAF5085E43BD91D6F0599F2BDE41" pageId="2" pageNumber="29" type="distribution and habitat">
<paragraph id="A9CDC58D6EAB01C20F905345B7A0BE37" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6D52C0D7F3C1D08879D084EDDA100D96" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicName id="AA128925C1A0235337470CC753A54A57" authorityName="Droissart, Stevart &amp; P. J. Cribb" authorityYear="2014" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Distylodon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asparagales" pageId="2" pageNumber="29" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sonkeanum">
<emphasis id="ABF5404AA4B27B4AAC3D14DA9F797D35" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">Distylodon sonkeanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to the coastal part of the Lower Guinea Domain (
<bibRefCitation id="C4DB2539691EFEFE62EA95B770B6F621" author="White, F" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin du Jardin botanique national de Belgique" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" pagination="11 - 55" refId="B11" refString="White, F, 1979. The Guineo-Congolian Region and its relationships to other phytochoria. Bulletin du Jardin botanique national de Belgique 49: 11 - 55" title="The Guineo-Congolian Region and its relationships to other phytochoria." volume="49" year="1979">White 1979</bibRefCitation>
) of the Guineo-Congolian Region. It is known from a single locality in South Region of Cameroon (
<figureCitation id="CDF35983D807FB17F62B9767F069DAC9" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Distribution of Distylodon sonkeanum and Distylodon comptum in tropical Africa." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/10631" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). The only population known so far was found in the lowland evergreen forest at 100 m elevation, growing epiphytically on a fallen branch.
</paragraph>
